10/06/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Experts began exhuming bodies from a mass grave near the eastern town of Bratunac on Wednesday (June 9th).
The site was discovered on May 25th during construction work in the area.
The victims are believed to be Bosniaks killed by Bosnian Serb forces at the beginning of the 1992-1995 conflict.
(Fena, BHRT, RTRS, AP - 09/06/10)
